This bar is awesome. My friends and I went here on our last day of visiting  Chicago, and we did not regret it. First of all the drink were good and inexpensive. The bar tender was so sweet to us ( i unfortunately don't remember her name), but she had great conversation and helped me figure out what i want to drink for the night. They have what looks like a 10-piece band, that sing a bunch of their own songs and then take request the other half of the night. When i say that band is amazing, they are AMAZING! They sung a lot of blues, jazz, and older R-n-b songs. After they're done they go into the crowd and mingle with everyone on the floor and at the bar. We met the owner right before we left and he was just as nice and courteous as all of his other employees. I can't wait to go back the next time i visit Chicago. I definitely recommend this spot for anyone who's looking for a really home-y, friendly environment.
